  "text": "A total of 2 ϫ 10 5 S2 cells per well were plated onto poly-lysine-coated Labtech chamber slides and transfected on the following day with a total of 300 ng DNA using Effectene (QIAGEN) according to the manufacturer's instructions. After 48 h, cells were fixed with 4% PFA for 10 min at room temperature and stained as described previously . The RNAi knockdown experiment was performed according to published protocols [CITATION_1] . Sequence of the Wnt5 dsRNA was provided by L.G. Fradkin (Petrova et al., 2013) . As negative control, we used a dsRNA targeting bel (a gene with no known function in PCP) (primers: 5Ј-GGATCCTAATACGACTCACTATAGGGCACCAGACCCAAC GGATA-3Ј and 5Ј-GGATCCTAATACGACTCACTATAGGGCCCGAACAT CACATCGTT-3Ј). Primary antibodies used were mouse ␣-Flag M2 (Sigma), mouse ␣-Myc 9E11 (1:500) (Santa Cruz Biotechnology), rat ␣-HA (1:250) (Roche), rabbit ␣-GFP (1:400) (Invitrogen), and rabbit ␣-WNT5 (1:2500) (kindly provided by L.G. Fradkin). Corresponding Alexa-488, -568, and -647 coupled secondary antibodies (Invitrogen) were used at 1:600.",
